<paragraph blockId="15.[168,775,1819,2091]" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1999,2023]" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">Identification.</emphasis>
Ocelli colorless, 1–2 per leaf, located suprabasally and arranged side by side, rarely in a row, generally larger than adjacent cells. This species is often
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[811,1419,160,326]" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">
confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[978,1195,160,184]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Prionolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="984" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[978,1144,160,184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">Prionolejeunea</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
due to the crenulate or denticulate leaf margins, but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="V.Schiffner" authorityYear="1893" baseAuthorityName="Spruce" box="[1186,1352,194,218]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Prionolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="984" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1186,1352,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">Prionolejeunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ocelli are absent. Briocenological group: corticolous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[811,1419,160,326]" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,999,267,292]" pageId="15" pageNumber="984">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
AM, BA, MG, MT, PA, PE, RJ, RO, SP (moderate distribution).
</paragraph>
